Name: RCS PRESSURIZATION
checklistText:
<size=21>RCS PRESSURIZATION</size>

1.
PANEL 3:	HTR CONT:
		TEMP MON sel - RCS QUAD 1, 2, 3, & 4
		TEMP ind - 120 to 145 F (for each quad)

2.
PANEL 2:	RCS:
		A & B QUANTITY ind - 100%

3.	RCS:
		TEMP/PRESS MON sel - He
		A & B PRESS ind - 2820 to 3280 psia

4.	RCS:
		TEMP/PRESS MON sel - PRPLNT
		A & B TEMP ind - 40 to 100 F
		A & B PRESS ind - 10 to 50 psia

5.	RCS:
		TEMP/PRESS MON sel - FUEL MANF
		A & B PRESS ind - 25 to 90 psia

6.	RCS:
		TEMP/PRESS MON sel - OXID MANF
		A & B PRESS ind - 25 to 90 psia

			CAUTION
		RCS SYS A & B ASC FEED 2 vlvs
		must be closed immediately after
		ED: RCS He PRESS sw - FIRE, to
		prevent possible propellant transfer
		between APS & RCS.

7.
PANEL 16:	CB ED: LOGIC PWR B - open
PANEL 8:	ED:
		MASTER ARM sw - ON
		RCS He PRESS sw - FIRE
PANEL 2:	RCS:
		SYS A ASC FEED 2 sw - CLOSE
		SYS B ASC FEED 2 sw - CLOSE
PANEL 8:	ED:
		MASTER ARM sw - OFF
PANEL 16:	CB ED: LOGIC PWR B - close

		CAUTION
	CB ED: LOGIC PWR A & LOGIC PWR B
	must be closed at completion of
	this task.

PANEL 1:	RCS A REG warn lt - off
	RCS B REG warn lt - off

8.
PANEL 2:	RCS:
		SYS A ASC FEED 1 sw - ASC FEED 1
		SYS B ASC FEED 1 sw - ASC FEED 1
		CRSFD sw - CLOSE; tb - bp

9.
PANEL 2:	RCS:
		TEMP/PRESS MON sel - OXID MANF
		A & B PRESS ind - 175 to 188 psia

10.
	RCS:
		TEMP/PRESS MON sel - FUEL MANF
		A & B PRESS ind - 175 to 188 psia

11.
	RCS:
		TEMP/PRESS MON sel - PRPLNT
		A & B TEMP ind - 40 to 100 F
		A & B PRESS ind - 178 to 188 psia

12.
	RCS:
		TEMP/PRESS MON sel - He
		A & B PRESS ind - 2750 to 3200 psia

13.
	RCS:
		A QUANTITY ind - record % remaining_____%
		b QUANTITY ind - record % remaining_____%
